on The second day of the course will focus on methods of economic evaluation We will first consider managerial studies and the reference case described in the recommendations of the U S Public Health Service Panel on Cost Effectiveness in Health and Medicine We will then turn to decision modeling and measurement of health care outcomes patient utilities In the afternoon session the groups will develop an outline of their chosen economic evaluation The final morning of the course will consider sources of data on health care utilization outside of the VA including Medicare and VA contract care We will hear presentations from the groups and conclude with a presentation on the role of economic evaluation in the health care system The course will end by noon on Friday 2003 20Seminar 20Series 20prelimin 20schedule pdf Click here to view the class schedule and a list of suggested readings Registration The deadline for registration has already passed but HERC will accept late registrations until August 8 To register e mail to mailto herc med va gov subject Seminar 20Series 20Late 20Registration herc med va gov or call HERC at 650 617 2630 Registrants should include contact information name address email address and telephone number and any topics of special interest Travel details Students are responsible for their own travel costs and arrangements including hotel reservations There is no charge for the course itself Students may obtain government rate lodging at the Stanford Terrace Inn 531 Stanford Avenue Palo Alto 800 729 0332 or 650 857 0333 see http www stanfordterraceinn com http www stanfordterraceinn com Mention the HERC course and give group number 94491 in order to receive the lower government rate which is 143 for a single and 153 for a double Reservations must be made by July 12 to receive the government rate The course will be held in building 205 at the Menlo Park campus of the VA Palo Alto Health Care System The campus is located at 795 Willow Rd in Menlo Park A shuttle will be provided between the Stanford Terrace Inn and the Menlo Park campus Students from out of the area can fly to either San Francisco SFO or San Jose SJC airports A shuttle from either location should take less than hour and cost about 45 Faculty Course faculty members are affiliated with the VA Health Economics Resource Center and or the Stanford University School of Medicine They are Paul G Barnett PhD Todd H Wagner PhD Mark W Smith PhD Wei Yu PhD Ciaran S Phibbs PhD Mary K Goldstein MD and Magda Berger MPH To view faculty bios Train Faculty htm click here Page Last Updated June 19 2003 http www va gov index htm Return to the Department of Veterans Affairs home page Department of Veterans Affairs VA Home Page http www va gov search Search the Department of Veterans Affairs Web site VA wide Search http www va gov General site map htm VA wide Site Map http www va gov facilities Contact information can be found on this site for Department of Veterans Affairs facilities Facilities Locator http www va gov disclaim htm Read the disclaimers of liability and endorsement Disclaimer http www va gov privacy Read about the privacy policy which addresses how this site uses cookies Privacy Security Statement http www va gov foia Browse the electronic Freedom of Information Act reading room Freedom of Information http www va gov accessible Accessible Electronic Information Technology Accessibility http www va gov customer consumer asp poc Find e mail addresses for Department of Veterans Affairs offices Contact the Department of Veterans Affairs VA About htm About HERC Sitemap htm Site Map Contact htm Contact Webmaster 
